In 2021, the eagerly awaited next instatement in the James Bond franchise will be realised as a shown in this slick trailer, but its release could be eclipsed at the box office by a movie most people in the West may never even have heard of, the slapstick comedy, ‚ÄúDetective Chinatown 3‚Äù will help China‚Äôs box office to take more than America‚Äôs, to become the biggest in the world.
For a century, Hollywood has ruled the movie world, now its China‚Äôs turn.
China‚Äôs cinema industry has been growing for a number of years, but in 2021, projections show‚Äôs America‚Äôs box-office revenue stagnating as China‚Äôs continues to rise.
In America, film fans are shunning the cinema of video-on-demand, but in China, both online streaming and cinema attendance are in the rise.
China‚Äôs rise to the top of the box office has been helped by the pandemic. Hollywood delayed productions and movie theatres has been closed. Yet in China, cinemas are now back up to almost 75% capacity and productions of new films is streaming ahead. Despite this, big American films still do very well in China, the eight installment of ‚ÄúThe Fast and Furious‚Äù series took nearly twice as much in China as it did in North America, but Hollywood reliance on Chinese tickets sales has started a worrying trend.
Tilda Swinton‚Äôs Marvel character in ‚ÄúDoctor Strange‚Äù, the Ancient One was changed from a Tibetan to a Celt, in part, it was thought, to placate China, but despite the soft power China may wield on Hollywood films, it‚Äôs unlikely it‚Äôll succeed in exporting its own blockbusters any time soon.

text:
I hereby request your candid and detailed response to the following questions: 

Dear Wayne Gates MPP Niagara Region and Premier Doug Ford and Wayne Redekop Mayor of Fort Erie
 
 
I know that you care deeply about the health and lives of citizens. I trust that your concern is broad-based and comprehensive, and that your concern extends to preventing deaths and adverse health outcomes, regardless of their source or cause. 
 
As you know, the lockdowns and social isolation measures imposed by governments on citizens risk throwing millions of Canadians into unemployment, bankruptcy or poverty, and in many cases all three. 
 
Social isolation, combined with unemployment and poverty, predictably lead to numerous adverse health outcomes: depression, anxiety, alcoholism, other addictions, drug overdoses, mental illness, obesity and suicides. 
 
You are no doubt aware that the cancellation of non-emergency surgeries, as well as the fear that patients now have of going to the hospital to obtain help, are causing adverse health outcomes, and in some cases death.
 
I trust that you have given very serious consideration to the number of lives that will be lost, as well as adverse health outcomes, as a result of the social isolation and economic devastation that government measures against COVID-19 are inflicting on citizens.
 
I hereby request your candid and detailed response to the following questions: 
 
1.	How many suicides are projected to take place as a result of the government having shut down much of our economy, forcing people into unemployment, bankruptcy, or poverty?
 
2.	How many do you project will die because of the rise in depression, anxiety, alcoholism, other addictions and drug overdoses that the lockdown and associated unemployment and social isolation will cause, as the lockdown drags on for weeks or even months? 
 
3.	How many children and spouses do you project will be abused while couples and parents remain confined to their homes, in many cases unemployed, without their usual income and social connections? 
 
4.	How many children will be put in foster care because of domestic abuse, or loss of their parents‚Äô ability to provide for them, or both? 
 
5.	How many isolated seniors are projected to become sick or die because they no longer receive regular visitors, such that nobody is able to take them to their own family doctor, or take them to an emergency unit at the hospital? How many will die at home, alone?
 
6.	How many people are projected to die or to suffer permanent damage because their non-emergency (elective) surgery, their testing and their various treatments have been cancelled due to your singular focus on fighting COVID-19? 
 
7.	How many people are projected to suffer serious harm caused by lack of access to secondary health providers they regularly rely on, such as physiotherapists, massage therapists, optometrists, chiropractors, osteopaths, podiatrists and dentists? 
 
8.	How many people are projected to die or suffer serious harm because they believe (correctly or incorrectly) that they cannot go see their doctor, or that they cannot check into emergency at the hospital?
 
9.	How many children, confined to their homes while schools and playgrounds are closed and athletic and recreational activities are shut down, are projected to develop diabetes or other chronic health conditions? 
 
10.	How many people will develop psychiatric disorders caused by governments having eliminated social interaction at restaurants, pubs, churches, recreational facilities and community centres? 
 
11.	Have you or your staff researched any of these questions here above? If yes to the foregoing question, have you created any models, estimates or projections in regard to any or all of these causes of illness, harm and death, in the same way that you have relied on models, estimates and projections in regard to COVID-19?
 
12.	If yes to the foregoing question, I request copies of those models, estimates and projections. If I receive no response to this letter, I will take that to mean that you and your staff have failed to calculate and consider the severe negative impact of the lockdown on the health and lives of citizens. 
 
I will have no choice but to conclude that no significant or meaningful research has been conducted on the crucial issues raised in this letter. 
 
I wish to remind you that your orders are violating citizens‚Äô Charter freedoms to move, travel, assemble, associate and practice their faith.
 
The onus is on government officials ‚Äì not on citizens ‚Äì to justify these violations of Charter-protected freedoms. 
 
I look forward to hearing from you. 
 
Yours truly,

text:
Are we doomed by the lazy minded easily led people who allow power crazed politicians to erase our freedom, earn a living wage and live a meaningful life? 

The lack of an alternative agenda to lockdowns is extremely worrying. Commenters here are promoting misinformation talking about a new Covid strain. It is a genetic variant, that is not necessarily a new strain. 

We still have no reliable data about how lethal COVID 19 really is. What we need to see is trusted all cause mortality data and have this compared with the previous 10 years. Sure we know COVID 19 is contagious and some people's lives have been shortened by it.

But is it the deadly killer it is portrayed to be? We have done immense other damage to society with our response to the pandemic, it seems to me to be disproportionate and irrational. I am not cold and uncaring about those who have lost loved ones. Families lose loved ones to all kinds of tragedies every day, it's a horrible fact of life on Earth.

We are we suddenly hooked on trying to halt the spread of an infectious virus whose fatality rate is not hugely different to that of seasonal influenza. We can argue about what the fatality rate is, but we don't have access to trustworthy data yet, but what is available does not support the fear and reaction currently seen.

What sort of World do those who hold the reins of power want to bring about? Their behaviour does not appear to be benevolent to the younger generation, what ever happened to the belief that the young are our future? I'm over 60 years old and I feel my generation has become too selfish, greedy and ignorant of the future World we are leaving. Reducing our demands on fossil fuel energy is one of the few meaningful advances we've made. Healthcare advances have been amazing but also creating a moral dilemma of extending the length of life irrespective of the quality of life leaving more and more to end their days with horrible diseases such as Parkinson's, dementia, incurable cancers and so on. It's definitely better to spend tax money on healthcare than warfare, but what about spending on better infrastructure, education, apprenticeships, cutting pollution especially plastics in packaging and so on.

I'd like to see people wake up and think about things more than just surface deep. Unfortunately I don't expect this to happen soon, hopefully I'm wrong. In the end nature will prevail, we are just a very advanced form of evolution that has possibly mutated too many times in the wrong direction and we are in the midst of some natural selection that will see a natural reset soon. 

In the absence of real change 2021 will usher in more of the same greed, vanity, brutality and what has happened for the past several thousand years. Have you realised as I have that we are the problem and our flaws are what brings us down.

text: Climate change is a global problem, yet only Europe and North America are doing anything about it. Developing nations can pollute as much as they want and it's fine because they're poor. Never mind their booming populations which brings me to my next point.. you can't tackle climate change the way we do unless you take into account population growth. People pollute and more people makes more pollution no exceptions. All you can do is do your best so that each person pollutes a little bit less, but if your pollution decreases by 50% while population grows 50%, you've gone nowhere pollution wise. And that's what the developing world is dealing with. You can argue per capita pollution in the west all you want, but that doesn't change the fact that China has double the emissions America does and that's because its population is 4x bigger. The best thing we can do for climate change is for the entire world to come together to help developing nations develop faster so birth rates can go down sooner rather than later.

text:
Junokaii 

A commercial greenhouse is not a natural environment. It is a controlled artificial monoculture and reliant on a larger Earth system, for healthy soil, water, weather, etc.

The earth system is very sensitive to temperature change, especially in polar regions. And with more CO2 but less forests and more acidic oceans the CO2 has nowhere to go, except for the atmosphere where it is trapping infrared radiations. The science is understood. 

A more apt metaphor would be: you pumped CO2 that was buried underground in a very large commercial greenhouse with all sorts of plants and trees and for a while you get higher yields, but every day you destroy a little more of the vegetation and diversity and lose some of your soil to erosion and desertification. 

How long before you had nothing left to eat?
